Cerro de Bonete, Sébaco Dist. Ca. 1000 m (c. 3200') alt. This stand is possibly at the most southerly limit of the natural range of Pinus oocarpa, growing on the hills W of the Rio Grande de Matagalpa. The stands are open due to felling & burning, with areas of grassland and bare rock. The parent rock is mainly rhyolitic (Tertiary volcanics); p.H. 6.0 Area is dry, with 922 mm (36'') rainfall p.a. The soil is extremely poor and thin and supports little vegetation other than pine. Humus almost totally absent.
